# fw_env.config — tells fw_printenv / fw_setenv (from u-boot-fw-utils) where
# the U-Boot environment lives. Matches the wks partition layout: two raw 1 MB
# partitions for primary + redundant env. We use the first 64 KB of each as
# the env area (CONFIG_ENV_SIZE = 0x10000 in U-Boot).
#
# Columns: device   offset   env_size   sector_size   #sectors
/dev/disk/by-partlabel/uboot_env    0x0000  0x10000  0x10000  1
/dev/disk/by-partlabel/uboot_envr   0x0000  0x10000  0x10000  1
